finalFix:
Replace the IQueryable build (lines 3857-3871) with a materialize-then-client-join, preserving output shape { id, user }. EF Core 10 cannot translate g.FirstOrDefault() (a non-aggregate row pulled from a group) used as a join key / in the projection (EF6 could). Materialize the grouped employee rows server-side (group key + a representative Id via a real aggregate), pull Users, then join/project in memory:

// EF Core 10 cannot translate g.FirstOrDefault() (non-aggregate row from a group) used as a
// join key or in the projection (EF6 could). Materialize grouped employees + Users, join client-side.
var emp = (from a in db.EmpAttendances
           where (From == null || From == "" || EF.Functions.DateDiffDay(a.login, crdate) <= 0) &&
                 (To == null || To == "" || EF.Functions.DateDiffDay(a.login, exdate) >= 0)
           group a by a.EmployeeName into g
           select new { EmployeeName = g.Key, Id = g.Min(x => x.Id) })
          .ToList();

var users = db.Users.Select(c => new { c.Id, c.UserName }).ToList();

var v = (from e in emp
         join c in users on e.EmployeeName equals c.Id
         where (user == null || user == "" || c.Id == user)
         select new { id = e.Id, user = c.UserName }).AsQueryable();

The rest of the method is unchanged: the search .Where(p => p.id.ToString()...) (line 3877), the dynamic .AsQueryable().OrderBy(sortColumn + " " + sortColumnDir) (line 3884), recordsTotal = v.Count() (line 3886), and v.Skip(skip).Take(pageSize).ToList() (line 3887) now run over the in-memory IQueryable and are safe.

Notes: (1) g.Min(x => x.Id) is the translatable, deterministic equivalent of legacy's g.FirstOrDefault().Id (a single representative Id per employee group); since the grid only displays/filters on id and user, output is preserved. (2) Apply the SAME fix to the duplicate at EmployeeAttendanceController.GetReport lines 567-581 â€” it carries the identical un-fixed pattern and 500s too (it is NOT a correct reference to copy from). (3) Group is guaranteed non-empty so the representative Id always exists; no null risk.
